<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06296134 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06296134 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  South Carolina Gov. Carroll Campbell has requested a state investigation intoallegations that former University of South Carolina President James Holdermanmade sexual advances toward male students. State Solicitor Dick Harpootlian,who was selected to conduct the investigation, immediately called on collegetrustees who served while Holderman was president to resign. Some trusteessaid they had heard allegations about Holderman but did not investigate them.&quot;If I was on the board . . . I'd feel compelled to resign,&quot; Harpootlian said.&quot;Not only did the board give Holderman carte blanche to mismanage theuniversity's finances, but (the board) also turned a deaf ear toward anyconduct.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  PROBE SOUGHT OF EX-COLLEGE HEAD'S CONDUCT  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  National News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911022  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  28C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  110  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday, October 22, 199100296134,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>